      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via residual drop (≥ 6 orders of magnitude for continuity, momentum, and scalar transport) and stabilization of NIH monitor point. Round-off error assessed via double-precision arithmetic confirmation and floating-point sensitivity test; no significant impact on NIH at operating conditions.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
